Contribute

  Contribution is allowed to any one how is interested in developing directly
 to the EngSB, adding documentation or developing connectors. The following 
 documentation describes where the infrastructure could be found an which should
 be done to contribute.
 
* Infrastructure

  The infrastructure in general is described {{{contribute/infrastructure.html}here}}.
  
* Documentation

  TBW

** Maven Site (this site)

  If someone likes to contribute directly to this homepace he/she can edit the
 code in the repositories doc project and contribute an patch (or directly) 
 commit to the source base. The documentation project could be found here: 
 {{http://85.126.79.3/svn/engsb/engsb/trunk/engsb-docs/src/site/}}. A more 
 detailed description about this could be found directly in the 
 {{{contribute/infrastructure.html}infrastructure documentation}}. The format 
 which should be written is APT (Almost Plain Text) and it could be found 
 {{{contribute/format.html}here}}.

** Docbkx (reference documentation)
  
  Docbkx is the maven library used to build doc-books. Docbook is the choosen format
 to write the reference documents, since its a completely opened format which could
 be easly managed by a source control management, edited without any special software
 and should work on each computer.
 
  TBW (additional docbkxs beside the reference doc)

